<paragraph blockId="14.[189,346,175,199]" box="[189,346,175,199]" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,346,175,199]" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">Comparazioni:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1180,213,329]" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">
L’edeago della nuova specie ha forma simile a quella dell’edeago di 
<taxonomicName authority="PACE, 1977" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1977" box="[900,1175,213,237]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Apalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circumflexa">
<emphasis box="[900,1044,213,237]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">A. circumflexa</emphasis>
PACE, 1977
</taxonomicName>
, dell’Ecuador, ma l’armatura genitale interna della nuova specie è esile, robusta in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1977" box="[1060,1173,244,268]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Apalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circumflexa">
<emphasis box="[1060,1173,244,268]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">circumflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e la porzione apicale distale dell’edeago, in visione ventrale, ha lati sinuati nella nuova specie e rettilinei in 
<emphasis box="[310,431,305,329]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicName authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1977" box="[310,427,305,329]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Apalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circumflexa">circumflexa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1179,357,411]" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,311,357,381]" pageId="14" pageNumber="147">Etimologia:</emphasis>
La nuova specie prende nome di «faticosa» perché ha richiesto faticoso lavoro per la sua determinazione.
</paragraph>
